<title>Chicken Noodle Soup</title>
<filename>chicken_noodle_soup.xml</filename>
<comment>Easy quick lunch!</comment>
<thumbnail>../images/chicken_noodle.soup.jpeg</thumbnail>
<category>Soup</category>
<ingredient>Water</ingredient>
<ingredient>2-3 chicken breasts chopped</ingredient>
<ingredient>1/2 cup parsley chopped</ingredient>
<ingredient>2 big carrots diced</ingredient>
<ingredient>2 sticks celery chopped</ingredient>
<ingredient>3 chicken stock cubes</ingredient>
<ingredient>2 rice noodle bundles</ingredient>
<ingredient>salt and pepper to taste</ingredient>
<step>Bring water to boil and add carrots, celery and stock cubes. Continue to boil for 10 minutes then add chicken, salt and pepper, and cook for a further 3-5 minutes. Add noodles and cook for 2 minutes. Lastly add parsley and serve immediately with crusty bread or toasted if desired.
    </step>
</recipe>

